findings.suggestion:
Option A (lightweight): Add a validateContextSource() function at the boundary where ContextSource is created, asserting 0 <= importance <= 1. Option B (type-safe): Define a branded type:

type Normalized = number & { readonly __brand: 'Normalized0to1' }
function normalized(n: number): Normalized {
  if (n < 0 || n > 1) throw new RangeError(`Expected 0-1, got ${n}`)
  return n as Normalized
}

Option A is more practical given codebase conventions.

